              "free_text": [
                " Experiment performed at the LBNL 88-",
                "inch cyclotron facility using the Berkeley gas-filled",
                "separator."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "208Pb target consisted of nine arc shaped segments,",
                "each with a 500-mg/cm2 thick lead layer sandwiched",
                "between layers of carbon with thicknesses of 40",
                "mu-g/cm2 facing the beam and 2 mg/cm2. These segments",
                "were mounted around the periphery of a 14-inch",
                "diameter wheel which was rotated to minimize thermal",
                "stress on the target from beam heating wheel which",
                "was rotated to minimize thermal stress on the target",
                "from beam heating."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Berkeley gas-filled separator (BGS) spatially",
                "separated the recoiling fusion evaporation residues",
                " (with E approx. 70 MeV) in flight from both beam",
                "particles and transfer reaction products on the basis",
                "of their differing magnetic rigidities within the",
                "separator's 0.88-torr helium atmosphere. The magnetic",
                "rigidity Br of the recoiling fusion evaporation",
                "residues (EVR) with Z=110 and A=271 was estimated to",
                "be 2.1 T m"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SISD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " EVR's were deposited at the BGS focal plane",
                "300-mm thick passivated ion implanted silicon",
                "detector with an active area of 116 mm (horizontal) x",
                "358 mm (vertical). Detector recorded the time,",
                "energy, and position of the implanted EVR's and of",
                "their subsequent alpha decays. Resistive charge",
                "division provided vertical position resolution within",
                "each strip"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PPAC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Parallel plate avalanche counter placed 24 cm",
                "in front of the strip detector, recorded the time and",
                "position of recoiling ions before implantation. The",
                "presence or absence of signals from ions passing",
                "through the PPAC distinguished beam-related events in",
                "the strip detector and those from the alpha decay of",
                "previously implanted ions."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Coincidence of PPAC and SISD within the",
                "position resolution indicated existence of correlation",
                "between evaporation residues and their alpha decay.",
                "EVR were identified by alpha decay sequences. Two",
                "decay chains were observed."
              ]
            }
          ],
